question.explanation:
Rates of work:
\[
A: \frac{1}{573},\quad B: \frac{1}{382},\quad C: \frac{1}{1146}
\]

Note that \(1146 = 2 \times 573\), so:
\[
\frac{1}{573} + \frac{1}{1146}
= \frac{2}{1146} + \frac{1}{1146}
= \frac{3}{1146}
= \frac{1}{382}
\]

Therefore total rate:
\[
\frac{1}{573} + \frac{1}{382} + \frac{1}{1146}
= \frac{1}{382} + \frac{1}{382}
= \frac{2}{382}
= \frac{1}{191}
\]

So together they take \(191\) days.

Let the total work be \(W\).

Time taken by \(B = 603\) days \(\Rightarrow\) rate of \(B = \dfrac{W}{603}\).

â€œA works twice as fastâ€ \(\Rightarrow\) rate of \(A = 2 \times \dfrac{W}{603} = \dfrac{2W}{603}\).

Combined rate:
\[
\dfrac{W}{603} + \dfrac{2W}{603}
= \dfrac{3W}{603}
= \dfrac{W}{201}
\]

So together they finish the work in \(201\) days.
